keyPolicies.policyDescription: Stop the sell off of council homes to private developers who make massive profits; Continue improving our homes and getting better value for money from repairs; Set up a tenants and leaseholders panel to give local residents a voice at the town hall; Stop the privatisation of caretakers on estates.

mentions.tacticalSituation: In the 2008 London and 2009 European elections the Tories came second in Camden, beating the Lib Dems.

housing.content: Stop the sell off of council homes to private developers. Continue improving our homes for better value from repairs. Set up a panel for tenants and leaseholders. Stop privatisation of caretakers on estates.

images.caption: Bar chart showing Labour, Tory, Greens, and Lib Dems vote counts in Camden from list section, London elections 2008.
